<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="172" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Comments</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="172" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">
Two adult females were collected from the Oasis Water Camp running among outbuildings and on rocky slopes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Broadley, DG" journalOrPublisher="African Journal of Herpetology" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="43 - 58" publicationUrl="10.1080/21564574.1998.9650002" refId="B22" refString="Broadley, DG, Bauer, AM, 1998. A review of the Mabuya quinquetaeniata complex in East Africa (Sauria: Scincidae). African Journal of Herpetology 47: 43 - 58, DOI: 10.1080/21564574.1998.9650002" title="A review of the Mabuya quinquetaeniata complex in East Africa (Sauria: Scincidae)." url="10.1080/21564574.1998.9650002" volume="47" year="1998">Broadley and Bauer (1998)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from a handful of records from the northern Mozambique, presumably based on records collected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Blake, DK" journalOrPublisher="The Journal of the Herpetological Association of Rhodesia" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="31 - 46" publicationUrl="10.1080/0440730X.1965.9650549" refId="B5" refString="Blake, DK, 1965. The fourth Umtali Museum expedition to Mozambique: November -December 1964. The Journal of the Herpetological Association of Rhodesia 23: 31 - 46, DOI: 10.1080/0440730X.1965.9650549" title="The fourth Umtali Museum expedition to Mozambique: November - December 1964." url="10.1080/0440730X.1965.9650549" volume="23" year="1965">Blake (1965)</bibRefCitation>
. Our record from Mt. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="M’pàluwé">M'paluwe</normalizedToken>
just fills in the gap between 
<bibRefCitation author="Blake, DK" journalOrPublisher="The Journal of the Herpetological Association of Rhodesia" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="31 - 46" publicationUrl="10.1080/0440730X.1965.9650549" refId="B5" refString="Blake, DK, 1965. The fourth Umtali Museum expedition to Mozambique: November -December 1964. The Journal of the Herpetological Association of Rhodesia 23: 31 - 46, DOI: 10.1080/0440730X.1965.9650549" title="The fourth Umtali Museum expedition to Mozambique: November - December 1964." url="10.1080/0440730X.1965.9650549" volume="23" year="1965">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Blake’s">Blake's</normalizedToken>
(1965)
</bibRefCitation>
Morrumbala and Nampula 
<pageBreakToken pageId="9" pageNumber="172" start="start">records</pageBreakToken>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Portik, DM" journalOrPublisher="Herpetological Review" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="394 - 406" refId="B53" refString="Portik, DM, Mulungu, EA, Sequeira, D, Mcentee, JP, 2013a. Herpetological surveys of the Serra Jeci and Namuli massifs, Mozambique, and an annotated checklist of the southern Afromontane archipelago. Herpetological Review 44: 394 - 406" title="Herpetological surveys of the Serra Jeci and Namuli massifs, Mozambique, and an annotated checklist of the southern Afromontane archipelago." volume="44" year="2013 a">Portik et al. (2013a)</bibRefCitation>
also recorded this species from Lichinga further north and Branch et al. (2005) recorded them from Niassa Game Reserve.
</paragraph>
